channel.title: I cant tell which router i have?!
channel.description:
i cant figure out which router i have.. how can i figure out what it is.. i dont have the box , manual , and the stickers on the back dont tell me much...
(i cant port foward ) :([br][size=1]Posted at: December 17, 2006, 04:23:31 AM[/size][hr]do u need to port foward? what does it do?

item.title: I cant tell which router i have?!
item.dc:creator: @Mrquarter Mrquarter
item.description:
@Mrquarter wrote:

You do not need to know your router name. Just put in your web bar 192.168.1.1 or 192.168.2.1 without the www. or .com. That will get you connected to your router so you can port forward.

Read full topic

item.title: I cant tell which router i have?!
item.dc:creator: @metalus89 metalus89
item.description:
@metalus89 wrote:

go to start, run, type in cmd, then type in ipconfig, then it will tell you your router name and your gateway ip address.
